description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Come and work for an independent healthcare company whilst still nursing NHS Cardiac Patients!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;InHealth have a Registered Nurse vacancy in the Cardiac Cath Lab Unit at St Peter’s Hospital, Chertsey, Surrey, just 5 minutes’ drive away from junction 11 of the M25&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our 20+ year service at site works in collaboration with the Trust to provide a seamless cardiac pathway for our patients. The CQC has rated the service as ‘GOOD’.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a very competitive annual salary, which is significantly enhanced by working as part of the on-call team for acute cardiac emergencies (subject to completion of your probationary period). Approved on call rates are better than those offered in the NHS!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A typical week would involve three long days (7.30am-6pm) and one half-day (6 hours) worked between Monday and Friday, 36 hours per week in total.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Last year’s InHealth annual staff survey in 2019 demonstrated that 95% of all who responded believed that patient safety was a top priority for InHealth, with 91% also believing that equality &amp; diversity is valued. In addition, 90% of staff thought that InHealth focusses on improving patient care and experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical training and professional development are a top priority with opportunities for career progression to senior clinical and management roles. There is an established leadership and management training programme available and in 2019 the average training days per person was 4.5 days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional benefits include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Private Healthcare with BUPA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid hospital car parking on site&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid NMC annual subscription&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid attendance at study days/courses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comparable contributary pension scheme where InHealth pays 5% of your annual salary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Life assurance (Death in Service benefit)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access 24/7 to an employee assistance programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhanced Maternity &amp; Paternity pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional flexible benefits can include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dental Cover&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discounted Gym Membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Childcare vouchers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cycle to Work scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Various discount schemes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Critical Illness cover&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;And much more!!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What skills and experience will you need to apply?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You must be a Registered Nurse level 1 or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have sound computer literacy with accurate data entry skills and attentionto detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report and audit writing skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use of advanced clinical skills in emergency situations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A keen interest in Cardiology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;A full Job Description and person specification is available upon request, we would love to hear from you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Apply now, or call us for more information or to arrange an informal visit&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
